and articles to the Times Literary Supplement for nearly forty years. She had a romantic friendship with the writer Vernon Lee and two happy – and celibate – marriages. Her salons in London and Paris were attended by major literary and artistic figures, and she counted amongst her friends Robert Browning, Oscar Wilde, John Addington Symonds, Gaston Paris, Ernest Renan, and Maurice Barrès.Reflecting a decade of research in international archives and family papers, A. Mary F. Robinson reveals the extraordinary woman behind the popular writer and critically acclaimed poet.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAuthors, Englishy19th centuryvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Literary.2bisacsh  aAestheticism.  aAnglo French.  aBiography.  aDecadence.  aDreyfus Affair.  aEdmund Gosse.  aEmile Duclaux.  aEmmanuel Berl.  aGender Studies.  aJames Darmesteter.  aJohn Addington Symonds.  aMabel Robinson.  aMarie Leneru.  aNeurasthenia.  aRobert Browning.  aSalon.  aSociety.  aTLS.  aTravel Journalism.  aVernon Lee.  aVictorian Poetry.  aWM Rossetti.  aWar Poetry.  aWomen Poets.  afindesiecle.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311127221408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021z978311127464540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780228010135?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780228010135423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780228010135/original  a978-3-11-127221-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-127464-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles